// CC0: Pretty ok post processing?
// Virgill and I released 'mrange & virgill - Delusions of mediocrity (Windows 4k intro)' at Deadline 2023
// https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgWmJAZIsXo

// The work is a combination of Vertex and Fragment shader but AFAIK shadertoy has no vertex shading support
// But I thought I share the post processing shader we used in the hope it helps someone.

// Music by Virgill.

// Shader being post processed by kishimisu: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mtyGWy

#define TIME        iTime
#define RESOLUTION  iResolution
#define PI          3.141592654
#define TAU         (2.0*PI)
#define ROT(a)      mat2(cos(a), sin(a), -sin(a), cos(a))

#define PREV_PASS   iChannel0
#define PREV_FRAME  iChannel1


const vec3
  L = vec3(.2, 1., .114)
, U = vec3(0.,1.,2.)
;

// License: Unknown, author: Matt Taylor (https://github.com/64), found: https://64.github.io/tonemapping/
vec3 aces_approx(vec3 v) {
  // Used to map color valus in [0, Inf[ range to [0,1] range
  v = max(v, 0.);
  v *= .6;
  const float a = 2.51 , b = .03 , c = 2.43 , d = .59 , e = .14;
  return clamp((v*(a*v+b))/(v*(c*v+d)+e), 0.0, 1.0);
}

void mainImage(out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord) {
  vec2 q = fragCoord/RESOLUTION.xy;

  float ptime = TIME;
  float ntime = floor(ptime/12.0);
  vec2 AA = 8.0/RESOLUTION.xy;
  vec2 pp  = -1.+2.*q;
  vec3 col = vec3(0.);
  float ft0 = mod(ptime, 12.)-6.;
  float ft = 6.-abs(ft0);
  float pfade = smoothstep(6./8., 0., ft+.25*((pp.y*pp.x)+.5*pp.y)); 

  vec2 p = pp;
  p.x *= AA.y/AA.x;

  float eff = -1.0;
  if (ntime == 3.0) {
    eff = 0.0;
  } else if (ntime == 5.0 || ntime == 7.0) {
    eff = 0.5;
  }

  float pmul = 1.;
  if (eff >= 0.) {
    vec2 nnn  = vec2(sqrt(.5));
    vec2 nn   = nnn.yx;
    nn.y *= -1.0;
    float off = ptime*.4 +dot(nn, p) + eff*sin(dot(nnn, p)+ptime);
    pmul = smoothstep(0., 1., fract(off));
    q += nn*.125*(1.-pmul);
  }

  vec3 pcol = pmul*texture(PREV_PASS,q).xyz;

  pcol = mix(pcol + pfade*(2.+.25*U.yxz), pcol*(1.-pfade), .5+.5*sign(ft0)) ;

  // "CRT" like line effect
  // Not attempting to be accurate in anyway
  pcol *= .75+.25*sin(TAU*(pp.y+U/3.)/AA.y);
  pcol *= smoothstep(48., 42., abs(ptime-48.)+4.*length(p));

  const int c = 4;

  pp *= .975;

  vec2 pq = .5+.5*pp;

  vec2 start = pq-float(c)*AA;
  vec3 bcol = vec3(0); 
  for (int y = -c; y <= c; ++y) {
    vec2 pp = start;
    for (int x = -c; x <= c; ++x) {
      vec3 fcol = texture(PREV_FRAME, pp).xyz;
      bcol += fcol;
      pp.x += AA.x;
    }

    start.y += AA.y;
  }

  bcol /= float((2*c+1)*(2*c+1));

  col = pcol;
  float l = dot(bcol, L);
  col = aces_approx(col);
  col += bcol*mix(vec3(.7, .5, .9), vec3(.6, .3, .4), l*l);
  fragColor = vec4(col, 1);
}

